This is it, your final assignment. Ready for the challenge?

For this assignment, you will need to compute barycentric coordinate on a triangular surface and complete several color shaders, including Flat shading, Ground Shading and Phong Shading.

We have prepared the code boilerplate. you'll need to complete some missing code.

Template codeï¼šunder folder of "HW4/"

Introduction
The interface and the controls are almost the same as the previous lab(HW3). Except for some changes:

The camera and light are now GameObject, which means they are adjustable in the hierarchy, these objects will be automatically added to the scene on startup.
Notice the material button? You can switch between different shaders which you'll be implementing later.
You can now change the color of the light and the object. Further implementation is needed.
You can also adjust the intensity of light.
Precondition
First, you need to paste your code you have written from your previous assignments. We have marked the parts you need to paste (TODO HW1, TODO HW2 or TODO HW3) in these files:

HW4
Camera
GameObject
util
If you paste the code correctly, you should be able to upload the obj model into the program. Currently you could only see the shadow of the models.



