Bonus: Texture Shader
Difficulty : â˜…â˜…â˜…â˜…â˜…

For this task, please inherit a new material and shaders on your own to complete the texture shader. It should be able to load in the texture and apply it to objects.
We have provided the UV coordinates in Mesh, which can be directly passed into the shader.



Elon_Musk_head / cat

Texture files are placed under data/textures/ directory.

Score
Each assignment's grading is divided into two parts: fundamentals and advanced.

Grading
FUNDAMENTAL

(25%) Correctly implement the barycentric.
(25%) Correctly implement Phong Shading.
(25%) Correctly implement Flat Shading.
(25%) Correctly implement Gouraud Shading.
BONUS 


[+1.5 Semester Score] Successfully implement Texture Shading OR Done something COOL AND GOOD.
Note

(The report credits 25% for each tasks)

Submission
After completing the assignment, please attach a README.md file and write down

which tasks you have completed
some screenshots of your work
how you completed these tasks (explain key code snippets, algorithms used or your finding, etc.)
If you have completed the assignment with the assistance of LLMs (e.g. ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Llama, Hatsune Miku, etc.), please also briefly describe how you utilize them in your report. (Using these and reporting honestly will not affect your score.)

Ensure that your code works in your environment before submission, otherwise, it will be considered non-functional and receive a score of 0. 


You can submit your work either by sending a github link of your project (be sure to set it to public), or simply attaching a zip archive (format: {StudentID}_HW4.zip).